Attention: CISD Virtual Learners ONLY
The Curbside Lunch order form has been updated! Go to our website, click on "Virtual Learners Back to School Information" and scroll to the bottom of the form. You must now select the menu of the campus your child attends. The state also changed pick-up locations. Parent will now be required to pick-up lunch orders from each campus their child attends. If you are ordering a lunch for your child who has chosen the Virtual Instruction plan, we are no longer able to use one location for pick-up.
All orders must be submitted by 8:30am each morning. Meals will be charged according to the student's eligibility. Campus pick-up locations are as follows:
Primary - North side of building
Lykins Elementary - South parking lot
O'Dell Elementary - West parking lot
6th Grade Center - East side of building
Junior High - West side of building
High School - East side of building under awning
For more information, please contact Director of Food Services Ofelia Almendarez at 469-742-9100 est. 1109.

post_text:
Hello Bobcats, this is Tom Maglisceau, Superintendent of Celina ISD:
It has been wonderful to see your children again, and I want to celebrate and thank our teachers for welcoming our students and families, while teaching both in-person and virtually. As we now move into our first full week of instruction, if your child is learning on a virtual plan and you wish to revert to in-person instruction, please reach out to your campus principal, so they can be aware of your intent and inform you of the steps you would need to take to move to in-person instruction. Families wishing to make this change must notify their campus principal by 5:00pm, Monday, August 24th. Beginning Tuesday, August 25th, all students must remain on their chosen virtual or in-person learning plan throughout the first nine weeks grading period.
Thank you for your continued support!

post_text:
Lykins Elementary Parents...
The Lykins Elementary campus is again experiencing connectivity issues. SuddenLink crews were out last night, but the issue was not resolved. Mayor Terry and the City of Celina are working with the district to restore internet to the building as quickly as possible. Thank you for your patience and understanding as we work together to resolve this issue. Due to the phones also being inoperable at this time, please call 972-948-1061 or you can also call Celina ISD Administration Building at 469-742-9100.
**The city has provided mobile hotspots, which will allow for connectivity while crews are working to fix the issue.

post_text: Life in Celina Podcast with Dr. Tom Maglisceau.
shared_text:
Life In Celina TX
July 21 at 10:40 PM ·

Tom Maglisceau took over the reins at Celina ISD during a global pandemic. The new superintendent has taken it all in stride, and is excited to call Celina, Texas, home. Now, Dr. Tom – as he's affectionately known around town – is ready to get back to learning. On this episode of "Life in Celina," Dr. Tom shares his story ... he discusses his new role with Celina ISD ... and he talks about what he's most excited about in Celina, Texas.
.
.
.
#lifeconnected #lifeincelina

A message to our "New" Celina ISD Families!
Many of you have filled out the enrollment information that is available on our website. The next step is to receive information from the Campus Registrar in order to complete the enrollment process. These ladies just returned to their campuses this week and are updating records and preparing emails to go out to our new families, which will include a Parent Portal code. New students will not show up in Parent Portal until they have been entered into the system and a code has been sent to you. We ask for your patience as we prepare for the 2020-2021 school year.

June 22 at 3:53 PM ·

A complete count in the census can build our State’s political influence so we can increase our representation in Congress, drive policy and receive federal money to support our community’s infrastructure, schools, healthcare needs and much more. Imagine Celina in the coming ten years before the next census! Let’s all do our part to ensure our great State and City have the financial support we’ll need for growth and sound planning!

Happy Wednesday Everyone! Today is the Pre-K & Kindergarten In-Person Registration at Celina Primary School!!! Please click on the link for specific times and forms required for enrollment. Just a few reminders...
Visitors will enter through the front entrance at assigned times and exit through the North end of the campus.
All visitors must wear a mask to enter the school building.
Visitors will need to use hand sanitizer when entering the building. (Provided)
Campus personnel will be monitoring the number of visitors entering the building in order to maintain 6 feet separation at all times.
Only one person per household will be allowed to enter the building.
No children allowed.
Visitors will not have access to school restrooms.
We appreciate your understanding and patience as we follow the state guidelines to ensure the safety of our visitors and staff.

Good Morning CISD! Summer Conditioning Camp begins today. Directions for today...
1. Bring water - 44oz-Gallon (No water will be provided at camp)
2. Show up at your assigned time. Do not come early or late. Please stay in your car if you arrive early. Parents must stay in their cars at all times.
3. Enter Athletic Complex Main Entrance or the JH Field House Main Entrance.(JH Boys)
4. Temperature will be checked. You will be screened for COVID symptoms.
5. You will go to an assigned location given to you at the temperature check station. Maintain 6ft distance between all persons at all times.
HS Boys - 10 grade-6:15am, 11th grade-6:20am, 12th grade 6:25am
All Girls - JH Girls-7:50am, HS Girls-7:55am
JH Boys - 8th grade-7am, 7th Grade-8:30am
9th FB/All Non-Football - 9th FB-8:50am, Non-Football - 8:55am
https://celinaisd.formstack.com/forms/summer_conditioning_camp_2020
If you haven't registered for camp, please click on the link provided. For more information, contact CISD Assistant Athletic Director Kyle Sheridan at kylesheridan@celinaisd.com.

Bobcat Nation - Census Update!!
Celina's response rate is at 59.3%. The State of Texas is at 47.3%. Things you should know...
A complete count establishes the base for demographics in our community and helps businesses decide where to locate and/or expand, which leads to new jobs. This creates an expanded tax revenue, which takes the pressure off of homeowners and helps schools in our community.

Happy Tuesday to Everyone in CISD Land!!! Let's work on our mental health....
1. Practice deep belly breathing. Breathe in for a count of 4 and breathe out for a count of 5. Do this a few times a day.

2. Do an act of kindness. Small acts of kindness positively changes your attitude and think what it does for the recipient!

3. Exercise, eat healthy, and make sure you are getting enough sleep.

4. Gratitude - Find one thing to be grateful for each day.

5. FOCUS on what you can control! Let go and enjoy this crazy time!!
We've Got This Bobcats!!!

A message from the Stay Well, Texas campaign...

Common symptoms of COVID-19 are fever, dry cough, and shortness of breath. If you have mild symptoms, call your doctor and Stay Home. If you develop serious symptoms, such as trouble breathing, pressure in the chest, or bluish lips or face, call your doctor and seek medical attention immediately.
Just a reminder that many individuals with COVID-19 are asymptomatic, meaning that they show no signs of symptoms, but can be shedding the virus more than five to seven days prior to outbreak. Stay Well, Bobcats!

post_text:
A message from the Stay Well, Texas....
You hear it all the time during flu season: wash your hands to prevent the spread of flu. You may have heard the same advice to stop the spread of COVID-19. Washing your hands with soap and water breaks up the molecules of the virus and washes them away, preventing the virus from infecting you or others, but you must wash your hands thoroughly and vigorously for at least 20 seconds.
While it is important to wash your hands, it is also important to regularly disinfect frequently used surfaces. COVID-19 has been shown to live for up to three days on various surfaces. If you must leave your home for essential services, be sure to wash your hands as soon as you return and disinfect any surfaces you may have touched. APART WE STAND TOGETHER!

post_text:
Bobcat Nation,
Recently, CISD Athletic Director Bill Elliott sent a message through School Messenger reminding students and parents that all facilities are closed to include our athletic facilities.

We have noticed individuals on Old Bobcat Field. The gates are locked for a reason and that is to prevent individuals from congregating on our athletic fields. Parents, please help us monitor this. Our closure is to limit contact with others. Coach Elliott will be monitoring the cameras and will remove anyone that he sees inside our athletic facilities. CISD Police and City of Celina Police Departments have also been notified.
CISD will abide by the guidelines set through the CDC and the Texas Department of Health during the duration of this closure.

post_text:
CISD Families & Community members,
Please read the following press release in regards to the name change to Celina Elementary. CES Principal Starla Martin stated in an email to her faculty and staff yesterday, "I understand that it is time to establish our own identity, just as other schools in the district will do or have done." She went on to say, "It is a beautiful reminder to all, as we should try to emulate Marcy's spirit and love for her student, peers, family and community!"

Attention: Celina Elementary Parents

Celina Elementary is experiencing sporadic power outages today. The district was made aware that an electrical grid is down, which is causing the disruption in power to not only Celina Elementary, but to 1500 homes in the area. Oncor is responding and is hopeful that power will be fully restored by 2:00pm today, if not sooner. We appreciate your cooperation as we handle this unexpected power issue. If you have any questions, please feel free to contact Celina ISD Administration offices at 469.742.9100.

post_text:
ATTENTION: The following is an important message from Celina ISD.
The District was contacted today by Waste Connections, with whom we have a contract for district recycling and trash removal. The company attempted to empty a trash receptacle at one of our campuses, but experienced an issue when trying to compact the garbage. A lawn mower had been thrown into the dumpster causing the hydraulic cylinders to jam. Lawn equipment and furniture are not allowed for disposal in any of our campus trash receptacles due to the fact that they can jam and/or cause damage to the garbage truck. If this continues, the district will be forced to pay an additional charge for locking containers. The Celina ISD Police Department will be reviewing footage from security cameras at all campuses. If you are aware of individuals that are disposing items like the ones mentioned above, please make them aware that this is considered illegal dumping and charges can be filed.

Celina High School
February 11 at 4:23 PM ·

Congratulations to our Special Olympics' athletes for their competition finishes in Basketball at Lovejoy this week. We competed against individuals in the surrounding and local areas (including but not limited to: Sherman, Lovejoy, Anna, Blueridge, Denison, Prosper), in a variety of basketball skills for dribbling, shooting and passing. We were so blessed to receive so many compliments from Lovejoy for our return this year, as well as from parents and friends in attendance today. We are so proud of the young men and women that compete with us each event!
After a round of skills competition, our athletes had the following finishing places:
Barrett Bohall- 1st place in his division
Ryann DeYoung- 2nd place in her division
Sean Medellin- 2nd place in his division
Francisco Moreno- 1st place in his division
Dane Parsons- 1st place in his division
Baily Thacker- 1st place in her division
That concludes our Basketball competitions for this year. We are excited to begin working on our skills and talents for the Track & Field competitions this year beginning in April. Go Bobcats!

Chief Mark Metdker of the Celina Fire Department presented CISD Assistant Athletic Director and Head Trainer Kyle Sheridan with the Citizen Life Saving Award during their annual awards banquet held this evening. Kyle was honored for his quick action that ultimately saved the life of Mr. Dennis Bennett, who suffered a life threatening heart attack while officiating a regular season Celina Bobcats football game.
We congratulate Kyle on this distinguished and well deserved honor!

shared_text:
OurCelina
February 5 at 3:42 PM ·

ONLY 2 DAYS LEFT!
Don't miss out on sending your kiddo and/or a friend or teacher a sweet treat on Valentine's Day!!!

The kids LOVE THIS! I promise you! It's something they do every year. They are only $3 each and the money benefits Project Graduation which happens the night of graduation for CELINA SENIORS that encourages a drug and alcohol free celebration! So the money stays right here and benefits our kiddos and goes toward a GREAT cause!

My younger kids LOVE sending one to their friends and neighbors. I like sending them to teachers and office staff as well! You can send them to ANYONE! (Don't forget the Admin building, too!!!)

Just print this form (you can print as many as you need) and return to your child's school with a check or exact cash for the total. It's super easy and your kids will be SO EXCITED on Valentine's Day!

Thanks so much for supporting Project Graduation!

post_text: During the month of January, school districts across the State of Texas will be honoring those that serve on their school boards. Our Celina ISD Board of Trustees are an exceptional group of individuals that represent Celina with integrity and commitment. They are entrusted with overseeing decisions that impact our students. Their dedication doesn't begin and end with a board meeting. All of our board members have spent numerous hours in training to ensure that they stay up to date on the latest educational issues and policies. It has been said that a school district is only as good as its board members. If that is the case, Celina ISD is blessed to have these seven, driven Trustees that are a true reflection of the vision and future of our school district. Thank you to our Celina Board of Trustees for your commitment to our students, our parents, our faculty and staff members! If you see them around town, please thank them for their service to our school district.

CHS COMPETITIVE CHEER TEAM TO MAKE HISTORY!

On Friday, the CHS Cheer Team will make HISTORY as the first ever cheer squad from Celina to compete at the UIL State Spirit Championships at the Ft. Worth Convention Center. They will face over 80 4A schools. The squad is scheduled to perform at 9:03am, 10:08am, and 11:26am. The top 20 will advance to finals starting at 5:35pm. If you are in the area, they would love any and all support! The team will have a Cheer Show Off tonight starting at 6:30pm at the Rock City Cheer & Tumble located at 4295 County Rd. 86 STE. #120, Celina, TX. It is your time to shine! Good Luck Bobcats!!!
Photo Credit: Holly Farrow Phoytography

post_text: Please help CHS make a difference in the lives of Celina families this holiday season!
shared_text:
Celina High School
December 16, 2019 at 8:01 PM ·

Attention all Bobcats! This is the season for giving!! Our Christmas Food Drive is underway! We have the awesome responsibility to meet the needs of 150 families in the Celina area!!! Please be generous and bring food to your 4th period class TOMORROW!! The competition is on!! The two 4th period classes with the highest donation in weight will win a Happy New Year's party in January!! Use the following shopping list for wanted food items!! You can make an impact on a family this season! Thanks for all you do to bless our city at Christmas!! Please do not give commercial-sized packages of food!!

Food Items We Accept:

Cans of Meat (Tuna, Salmon, etc.)

Container of Peanut Butter

Cans of Beans

Cans of Corn

Cans of Green Beans

Can of Greens (Collards, Spinach, etc.)

Can of Carrots or Sub Another Item

Pasta

Pasta Sauce

Soups

Can of Fruit

Bag of Dry Beans

Rice (2 Lbs)

Macaroni & Cheese

Ramen

Breakfast Cereal

Mixed Vegetables

Thank you for your donations!

Celina High School
October 29, 2019 at 6:37 PM ·

Congratulations to our Special Olympics' athletes for their competition finishes in Bocce, located in Van Alstyne. We competed against individuals and teams in the surrounding and local areas, including but not limited to: Melissa, Van Alstyne, Denison, Prosper, S & S, Sherman, Pottsboro and Whitesboro.
After two games of competition, our partnered athletes had the following finishing places:
Barrett Bohall and Francisco Moreno- 3rd place in their division
Ryann DeYoung and Baily Thacker- 2nd place in their division
Lorenzo Rangel and Dane Parsons- 2nd place in their division
We are looking forward to our next athletic competitions in both Bowling and Bocce in the next two weeks! Go Bobcats!
